Ditlev Trappo Saugmand Bjerregaard (1852 in Højbjerg, Denmark – 1916 in Kjellerup, Denmark) was a Danish businessman, traditional musician and a prolific composer of traditional dance music.
He began composing in 1872 and published his first tune collection in 1878.

In 2000 a remembrance plaque was placed at his home in Kjellerup, inaugurated by the deputy mayor.
